{"questionId":"12698","questionHtml":"<p>Find the size of&nbsp;angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{A}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{C}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>A</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{250}}{{{\\text{sin}}\\,{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{A}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{C}}}} = \\frac{{387.015 \\ldots }}{{{\\text{sin}}\\,\\left( {125^\\circ } \\right)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>250</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>B</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mover>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>A</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>∧</mo>\n      </mover>\n      <mo>⁡</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>387.015</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mn>125</mn>\n            <mo>∘</mo>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong><strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{co}}{{\\text{s}}^{ - 1}}\\left( {\\frac{{{{185}^2} + 387.015{ \\ldots ^2} - {{250}^2}}}{{2 \\times 185 \\times 387.015 \\ldots }}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>co</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>s</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>185</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>387.015</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mo>…</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>250</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mo>×</mo>\n          <mn>185</mn>\n          <mo>×</mo>\n          <mn>387.015</mn>\n          <mo>…</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong><strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for substitution in the sine or cosine formulas; <strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong> for correct substitution.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{A}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{C}} = {\\text{31}}{\\text{.9}}^\\circ \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>A</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>31</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <msup>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>.9</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (31.9478…°)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><str